# ATC Monitoring System

## AWS ACCOUNT

- root email address: lira_2111@yahoo.com
- password: Atc@amazon2026
- REMINDER: Get GoogleAuthenticator for MFA

### Prerequisites

1. Key Pair - Create key pair in EC2, download `.pem` file

---

### Connecting to EC2

- EC2 Public IP: `54.169.216.182`
- After downloading `.pem` file
- use ssh from your computer to connect to EC2:
  - `ssh -i <KEY_PAIR>.pem ubuntu@54.169.216.182`

### Connecting to MySQL

- After connecting to EC2, type in this command:
- `mysql -h atc-monitoring-system.c72ka2agmalz.ap-southeast-1.rds.amazonaws.com -u admin -p`
- then input password `Atcamazon2026`

### Downloading Backup `.sql` file

- After connecting to EC2, type in this command:

```
mysqldump -h atc-monitoring-system.c72ka2agmalz.ap-southeast-1.rds.amazonaws.com -u admin -p \
  --single-transaction \
  --set-gtid-purged=OFF \
  --quick \
  --routines --triggers --events \
  atc_monitoring_system > backup.sql
```

- this command will create a `backup.sql` file in your ec2
- exit EC2, then type in your local computer this command:
- `ssh -i <KEY_PAIR>.pem ubuntu@54.169.216.182:~/backup.sql .`

## Restarting Server

- type in command `pm2 restart 0 --update-env`
